# Title: Suspicious Child Process Created as System
# Author: Teymur Kheirkhabarov, Roberto Rodriguez (@Cyb3rWard0g), Open Threat Research (OTR)
# Date: 2019-10-26
# Level: high
# Description: Detection of child processes spawned with SYSTEM privileges by parents with LOCAL SERVICE or NETWORK SERVICE accounts
# MITRE Tactic: Privilege Escalation
# Tags: attack.privilege-escalation, attack.stealth, attack.t1134.002
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_susp_child_process_as_system_.yml

IntegrityLevel IN ("System", "S-1-16-16384") ParentUser IN ("*AUTHORI*", "*AUTORI*") ParentUser IN ("*\\NETWORK SERVICE", "*\\LOCAL SERVICE") User IN ("*AUTHORI*", "*AUTORI*") User IN ("*\\SYSTEM", "*\\Système", "*\\СИСТЕМА") NOT (CommandLine="*DavSetCookie*" Image="*\\rundll32.exe")